  <h2 id="whatIs">What is companion planting?</h2>
  
  <p>Companion planting is when two or more plants are grown near each other so that they will mutually benefit each other.  There are a variety of ways that plants can benefit each other while growing. Some plants may reduce pests for other plants or increase nutrients for another plant.  Other plants attract polinators, which results in better crop yeild.</p>
