  <h2 id="example">Companion Plant Examples</h2> <!--Three sisters method-->
  <p>The Three Sisters method was used by the Iroquois.  They planted beans, corn, and squash together.  The beans added nitrogen to the soil. The corn stalks provide support for the beans to grow upwards. The squash covers the ground, preserving the soil's moisture and preventing weeds. </p> <!--Add citation-->
  <p>The Three Sisters method is still commonly used today. </p>

