  <h2 id="commonCompanion">Common Companion Plant Pairings:</h2>
  <p>Here are a few common plant pairings: </p>
  <ul> <!--List of common companion plants-->
    <li>Tomato benefits from being planted with basil and a few other herbs. Basil repels common tomato plant bugs like whiteflies, spider mites, and aphids. Basil attracts polinators that benefit the plant. Calendula, dill, and thyme also repel tomato plant pests. Garlic is a natural pest repellant for tomato plants due to its strong odor. Asparagus can protect tomato plants from fungus from a natural fungicide that they produce. Tomato plants can also benefit asparagus plants by repelling asparagus beetles. </li>
    <br>
